{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1734a229-bcc2-4931-87c7-0a9751bd1c18","content":"Analyzing .dmp files is outside the scope of my available skills (the `dump-collect` skill covers only **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them). However, here's how you can investigate:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `pe -lines` | Print last exception with source lines |\n| `clrstack -all` | Managed call stacks for all threads |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM crashes) |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n\n**Using Visual Studio** (Windows):\n1. **File → Open → File** → select the `.dmp`\n2. Click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**\n3. VS will show the exception and call stack directly.\n\n**Using `lldb`** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\npe\n```\n\nWould you like help setting up any of these tools?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ce20c590-3898-453e-bd51-9649ac6b8b4a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is not appropriate here. The user needs help with dump *analysis*, not collection.\n\nLet me provide guidance on how to analyze the dump file.","outputTokens":422,"requestId":"ABC6:24FEAD:1476709:16F3858:6A0672DB"},"id":"f76ac589-7d0e-4f17-86f4-e013e90357df","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:12:06.638Z","parentId":"6c009442-9f9e-4861-bb74-85d3714d1f0c"}
